I"i<p>During //Build, Microsoft <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2017/05/10/with-cosmos-db-microsoft-wants-to-build-one-database-to-rule-them-all/">surprised the market</a> with the CosmosDb announcement. With the announcement, Microsoft made some very bold statements about the service, particularly about scalability and performance. I was particularly curious about the sub-10-millisecond write performance promised at the 99th percentile, which also included the indexing overhead on writes (see more about this <a href="https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/blog/a-technical-overview-of-azure-cosmos-db/">HERE</a>).</p>
